<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title><%= title %></title>
        <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    </head>
    <body bgcolor="#24273a" text="#cad3f5">

        <div class="center-content">
            
            <h1><%= title %></h1>
            <p>Welcome to my <%= title %> challenge</p>

            <hr />
            <center>

                <img src="/images/<%= title %>.png" alt="<%= title %>"  style="max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 0 auto;" />
            
                <p>During Module 5, I designed and built a working AC-to-DC power supply that converts 230V AC mains voltage into approximately 17V DC. The goal of this project was to deepen my understanding of electronics while gaining practical experience with more advanced circuit design.</p>
                <p>The project involved researching power supply design, creating the circuit schematic, sourcing components, and building and testing the final system. Throughout the process, I learned how to safely work with high voltages and apply theoretical concepts from Systems and Signals in a practical context.</p>
                <p>One of the biggest learning outcomes was developing confidence in handling more advanced electronics and understanding how different circuit stages work together. The design process went well, and the project was completed safely and successfully.</p>
            </center>
            
            <hr />
            <p><a href="https://kiliandiescher.org">Also check out my other projects on my portfolio!</a></p>
        
        </div>
    </body>
</html>